title: For Sale:  Full Box of Vintage .45 Ball Model 1909 Cartridges
postcontent: This is a great piece of old history for any ammunition collector. A FULL, SEALED box of twenty .45 Revolver Ball Cartridges, Model of 1909 for Colt's Double Action Revolver, Model 1909, smokeless powder! It was made by the Frankford Arsenal and is DATED March 28, 1914! Almost 100 years old and never opened! The box is in great condition with some very minimal age/handling marks. Just look at the pictures. It has the original factory cloth tape sealing the ends. This is the only box of this type of bullets that I have ever seen. I've had them in an air-tight container for over 30 years.

title: For Sale:  Beware of Scammer!!
postcontent:
Buyers, 

There is a repeat scammer that has been posting on here. He is posting guns at great prices (first warning sign). After you talk to him for a while, he will soon ask you to wire money (never wire money!).

Easy way to spot him is that all he is doing is pulling images from the internet and using direct text from the manufacturer website or retail/auction sites. He generally posts 2 guns at a time. Usually AR-15s, but lately he has tried just uppers and handguns. 

Beware of him and flag as a scam when you see. Seriously, the guy asks you to wire money over being paid in cash. Or offers you half price if you wire money.
